article_title: After 45 years, Walk-In Counseling Center still offers free therapy to all comers

article_metadata.description: In 1969, when Walk-In Counseling Center was founded, Minneapolis was a regional hub for the burgeoning youth movement. The city had become a gathering place for young people who had left their homes to create new lives. Those new lives were sometimes accompanied by trauma — Walk-In was created to address that very problem.

og.description: “Our philosophy remains, ‘Free, no-barriers, no appointment. If you come you will be seen,’ ” says Executive Director Mary Weeks.
og.title: After 45 years, Walk-In Counseling Center still offers free therapy to all comers
